title: @OspreyWTEN Closes Second Day at ITA Regionals
text: fell in their second round game to the No. 7 team from Georgia Tech, 8-1. In singles action, Vazquez won two matches in the consolation bracket, winning her Round of 32 match 7-5, 6-1 and her Round of 16 match 6-3, 6-3. "Quetzali played great tennis today and took down a solid player for Georgia in her second match," said coach . "I was impressed with her composure and focus throughout the day and I'm looking forward to watching her continued growth as a player tomorrow." Hemmerich fell in her Consolation Round of 32 match 7-6 (3), 6-3. "Despite the results, Noemi played better tennis this weekend. She is learning how she has to play and think in order to be a successful college tennis player and with a few more experiences/matches her results will improve," added Cohen. "She has a big game and a lot of room to grow." was also in singles play, winning her Round of 32 match 6-3, 6-3. Valdez advanced through the Round of 16, winning her match 6-2, 6-2. "Michelle struggled a bit with confidence but got through the day with a couple of W's which is a testament to how good her level is," added Cohen. "Tomorrow she has to let go of her fears and rip balls." The Ospreys are back in action tomorrow for their third day of competition at ITA Regionals.
